---
<Layout
  title="Plumbing prices in Pakenham 2026 | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Real 2026 plumbing prices in Pakenham — call-outs, blocked drains, hot water, burst pipes, gas. Honest ranges with no surprise fees. Call (03) 9003 0108 for an exact quote."
  canonical="https://pakenhamplumbers.com.au/pricing/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Honest 2026 pricing, no surprise call-outs</span>
      <h1>How much do plumbers charge in Pakenham? 2026 pricing guide</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Plumbing in Pakenham ranges from a $90 tap washer through to a $9,000 sewer reline, and most homeowners only ever see one number on a quote sheet without much sense of whether it's fair. This guide lays out what we actually charge across the most common jobs, what the price-changing factors are, and the 4 red flags that usually mean a quote is going to grow once the truck is in the driveway.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108" aria-label="Call (03) 9003 0108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a written quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <p class="lead">Every job is different — slab access, pipe age, council rules, parts availability — but the ranges below are typical for a licensed AU plumber working in Pakenham this year. Call (03) 9003 0108 for an exact quote based on your situation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Typical 2026 prices for plumbing services in Pakenham</h2>
      <p>Real ranges from our books, not made-up averages. Every quote we issue is itemised against the work below.</p>
        <table class="pricing-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical range (AU 2026)</th><th>What's included</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Standard call-out (business hours)</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$90 – $150</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Covers the first 15–30 minutes on site for diagnosis. Waived on most fixed-price jobs.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>After-hours / weekend call-out</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$180 – $300</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Surcharge on top of standard rates. Genuine emergencies only — burst, flood, no hot water with a baby in the house.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Tap washer / cartridge replacement</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$90 – $180 per tap</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Includes parts. Disc cartridge a bit more than rubber washer.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Blocked sink / basin / shower drain</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$150 – $350</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Hand-rod or short-eel clear-out. Trap removal extra if it's the trap blocked.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Blocked main drain (eel + CCTV)</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$350 – $750</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Electric eel to restore flow + CCTV camera to identify cause. Honest pricing on root-cut vs reline after that.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Pipe reline (no-dig CIPP)</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$250 – $450 per metre</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">50-year fix without excavation. Typical house-to-boundary 8–14m = $2,500 – $6,500.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Hot water service repair</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$220 – $550</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Element, thermostat, valve, anode rod swap-out. Same-day on most common units.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Hot water service replacement</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$1,500 – $3,800</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Includes unit, install, disposal. Heat-pump higher (rebate-net pricing on request).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Burst pipe — visible repair</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$220 – $550</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Single section, accessible. Includes water-off shut-down and reinstatement.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Burst pipe — under-slab</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$1,500 – $5,500</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Leak detection + breakout + repair + reinstatement. Insurance usually covers the make-good.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Toilet repair / cistern rebuild</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$180 – $420</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Cistern internals, flush valve, inlet valve.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Toilet replacement (supply + fit)</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$650 – $1,400</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Standard close-coupled to better-spec wall-faced. Includes removal of old + disposal.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Gas leak detection + repair</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$320 – $1,500</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Detection, repair, AS/NZS 5601 compliance certificate.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td data-label="Service"><strong>Gas appliance install (Type A)</strong></td>
              <td data-label="Price"><span class="price-range">$280 – $650</span></td>
              <td data-label="Note">Cooktop or hot water connection by licensed gasfitter. Compliance certificate included.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
