      <div class="cta-card-body">
        <h3>Need an exact price for your job?</h3>
        <p>Most quotes ready within 24 hours of the site visit. No-obligation, free, written.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-card-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Online quote form</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>What changes the price on your job</h2>
      <p>The ranges above are the starting point. These five factors are what move a quote up or down within (or sometimes outside) those bands.</p>
        <ol class="numbered-list">
          <li>Time of day — after-hours and weekends typically add 60–100% to labour. We always tell you on the phone whether your job is a genuine after-hours job or whether it can safely wait until 8am next morning.</li>
          <li>Access — under-slab, in-ceiling, second-storey, or limited-access cupboard work all add labour time. We assess this on the site walk before quoting fixed-price.</li>
          <li>Parts grade — Australian Standards-compliant Watermarked parts cost more than no-name imports but won't void your insurance. We only fit Watermarked.</li>
          <li>Council / water authority — some drainage work in Pakenham requires a permit or witness from the local water authority. We handle the paperwork and bake the fee into the quote.</li>
          <li>Job duration — a 30-minute fix runs at our minimum rate; a 6-hour job is quoted by the job, not the hour, so you know the number before we start.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-warn">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Red flags &mdash; what to watch for in quotes</h2>
      <p>We see these patterns every week from operators we'd never recommend. If a quote you've received contains one of these, ask before signing.</p>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Quotes given over the phone without a site inspection — almost always wrong by 30%+ once the truck is on site.</li>
          <li>'$0 call-out' that turns into a $300 diagnostic fee — read the fine print before you book.</li>
          <li>Unlicensed plumbers — illegal in Australia and voids your home insurance the moment they touch the pipes. Always ask for the licence number.</li>
          <li>Material mark-ups buried in the labour line — ask for an itemised invoice. A trustworthy quote separates labour from parts.</li>
          <li>'Cash discount' offers — usually means no warranty, no invoice, no recourse. Worth $0 if the job goes wrong in week 6.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>How to get an accurate quote in 5 minutes</h2>
      <p>Have the following ready when you call (03) 9003 0108 (or jot it on the quote form) and we can give you a real number in one call, not five.</p>
        <ol class="numbered-list">
          <li>A photo of the problem area (or the appliance label if it's a hot water / gas unit).</li>
          <li>Your meter / mains shutoff location if it's a leak or burst.</li>
          <li>The age of the home (or at least the decade) — pipe material changes the diagnosis.</li>
          <li>Whether the property is currently tenanted (changes our scheduling and access plan).</li>
          <li>Your access constraints — gates, dogs, building access codes, parking restrictions.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-tint">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Is the quote free?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — written quotes for any job we attend are free. We charge a standard call-out if we're diagnosing something specific (and waive it if you proceed with the job), but the quote itself is no-obligation.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Do you charge by the hour or by the job?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Most jobs we quote fixed-price after a site walk so you know the number before we start. For diagnostic work or repairs where the scope isn't clear up-front, we charge by the quarter-hour and stop to re-quote if the job grows.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Do you do after-hours emergencies?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — for genuine emergencies (burst, flood, no hot water with a baby/elderly resident, sewer overflow). After-hours rates apply. We'll be straight with you on the phone about whether it's a genuine emergency or can safely wait.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Are you licensed and insured?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — fully licensed under the relevant state plumbing authority and carrying $20 million public liability. Licence numbers visible on every invoice and quote.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Do you provide compliance certificates?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — Certificate of Compliance issued on every gas, drainage, and roofing job that requires one under AS/NZS 3500 or 5601. We lodge with the water authority where required.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Will the price grow once you start?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">Only if we hit something genuinely unforeseen (e.g. under-slab corrosion we couldn't see) — and we stop and re-quote with you before doing the extra work. No surprise invoices.</div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-q"><strong>Can I get an indicative price by phone?</strong></summary>
          <div class="faq-a">For some common jobs (washer replace, hot water swap), yes. For anything diagnostic or anything involving access, drainage, or gas, we need to see it before quoting — anyone who quotes drainage over the phone is guessing.</div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-card-section">
    <div class="cta-card cta-card-primary">
      <div class="cta-card-body">
        <h3>Ready for an exact quote on your Pakenham job?</h3>
        <p>Free written quotes. No obligation. Same-day callbacks on most enquiries.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cta-card-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="tel:+61390030108" aria-label="Call (03) 9003 0108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-large" href="/quote/">Get a quote online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>

    .lead { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 70rem; margin: 0 auto; color: var(--text, #1f2937); }
